about.summary: In-process task scheduler with Cron-like capabilities

name: apscheduler
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "APScheduler" %}
{%set version = "3.2.0" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash_val = "5baa1195ba711868fae257612cf80372ff1124014ca896884bf132f75636f638" %}
{%set compress_type = "tar.gz" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ compress_type }}
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - setuptools_scm
    - six >=1.4.0
    - pytz
    - tzlocal >=1.2
    - futures  # [py27]
    - funcsigs  # [py27]
  run:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - six >=1.4.0
    - pytz
    - tzlocal >=1.2
    - futures  # [py27]
    - funcsigs  # [py27]

test:
  imports:
    - apscheduler
    - apscheduler.executors
    - apscheduler.jobstores
    - apscheduler.schedulers
    - apscheduler.schedulers.blocking
    - apscheduler.triggers
    - apscheduler.triggers.cron

about:
  home: https://github.com/agronholm/apscheduler
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: In-process task scheduler with Cron-like capabilities
  dev_url: https://github.com/agronholm/apscheduler
  doc_url: https://apscheduler.readthedocs.io

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ddunwoody
    - synapticarbors
